<p>
The Water Environmental Hub began in 2010 with $1.8 million of seed funding over two years from Western Economic Diversification Canada, University of Lethbridge, and Cybera Inc..
</p>

<p>
The project is currently managed by <a href="http://www.explorus.org/">Explorus Data Solutions Inc.</a> (not-for-profit), <a href="http://www.cybera.ca/">Cybera Inc.</a>, <a href="http://www.tesera.com/">Tesera Systems Inc.</a>, and <a href="http://www.uleth.ca/">University of Lethbridge</a>. It is also supported by various water and environmental data organizations including the <a href="http://www.imagingcenter.ca/">Alberta Terrestrial Imaging Center</a>, <a href="http://www.albertatechfutures.ca/">Alberta Innovates Technology Futures - Energy and Environmental Solutions</a>, and <a href="http://www.seawa.ca/">SEAWA - South East Alberta Watershed Alliance</a>. The project is currently being funded by <a href="http://geoconnections.nrcan.gc.ca/">Natural Resources Canada - GeoConnections</a> and the <a href="http://www.canadaschoolofenergy.com/">Canadian School of Energy and Environment</a>.
</p>
